  "prompt": "What is the best thing a friend has done to you?",
  "response": "The best thing a friend has ever done for me can vary greatly depending on personal experiences, but many people cherish moments of profound support and kindness. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. **Being There in Tough Times**: A friend who stands by you during difficult moments\u2014whether it\u2019s offering a listening ear, helping you through a crisis, or just being present\u2014can make an immeasurable difference.\n\n2. **Celebrating Your Successes**: A true friend who genuinely celebrates your achievements, big or small, without envy or competition, can make you feel valued and supported.\n\n3. **Offering Unconditional Support**: Whether it\u2019s helping you move, driving you somewhere in an emergency, or sticking up for you when you\u2019re not around, acts of selfless support are unforgettable.\n\n4. **Keeping You Grounded**: A friend who tells you the truth, even when it\u2019s hard to hear, and helps you stay true to yourself is invaluable.\n\n5. **Remembering the Little Things**: A friend who remembers your favorite things, checks in on you when you\u2019re going through something, or surprises you with something thoughtful shows how much they care.\n\nFor me, the best thing a friend has done is simply being a constant presence\u2014someone I can always count on, no matter what. What about you? What\u2019s the best thing a friend has done for you?",
